Ministry of Health confirms 180th H5N1 case
-------------------------------------------
The Indonesia Ministry of Health, the General Directorate of
Infectious Disease and Environmental Health, through the National
Institute of Health Research & Development laboratory, confirmed an
additional H5N1 human case.

The victim is a 29-year-old female, resident of Bangli regency, Bali
province. She is a mother of 2 former H5N1 cases (5-year-old female,
and 10.5-year-old male).

The victim felt weakness, coughing, and breathing difficulty on 15 Oct
2011, and sought help at an emergency unit in the nearby regional
hospital. When she was about to be transferred to a referral hospital,
the victim escaped and was found at the place of an alternative healer
on the next day. Her condition was getting worse and she died in her
home on 17 Oct 2011.

Epidemiological investigation showed that the victim lived in area
where many people were rearing poultry. Also, the victim's family
owned flocks of poultry. This case brings the total number of H5N1
cases in Indonesia to 182 with 150 fatalities.

This case has been reported to WHO by the general director of
infectious disease and environmental health, Prof dr Tjandra Yoga
Aditama.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

